            <title>Husqvarna Turning to Lean Manufacturing</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	The world&amp;rsquo;s largest producer of lawn mowers, power tools and trimmer, Husqvarna,&amp;nbsp;knows a thing or two about cutting and pruning. When it came time for a more efficient approach to production at Husqvarna &amp;ndash; in this case, trimming production time at its plant in Beatrice, Neb. &amp;ndash; the company turned to Lean Manufacturing experts Rucker &amp;amp; Associates for impressive results. So impressive that Husqvarna recently invited Rucker to share its Lean manufacturing efficiency measures at the company&amp;rsquo;s largest U.S. site in Orangeburg, S.C.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	In recent years, growing customer demand necessitated improved efficiencies at Husqvarna&amp;rsquo;s Beatrice plant for the company to expand production. Implementing Lean Six Sigma strategies helped Husqvarna increase production capacity.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	According to David Rucker, the Beatrice production line features multiple equipment models, each requiring unique assembly methods and different amounts of dedicated assembly time from the operators. Using Lean principles to balance production flow, Rucker&amp;rsquo;s team created a more visual and flexible assembly line, delivering only the next two hours&amp;rsquo; worth of raw materials. Rucker is president of Rucker &amp;amp; Associates whose team specializes in finding industrial and operational efficiencies.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;ldquo;By changing the way operators worked on the line, we were able to make it easier for Husqvarna to accomplish more, increasing the overall efficiency,&amp;rdquo; Rucker said. &amp;ldquo;These types of changes make a huge difference in all aspects of the business, from reduced labor costs to on-time delivery.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	The Orangeburg site is next in line. According to Rucker, it provides a greater challenge simply because of the size of the plant, at&amp;nbsp;1 million square feet.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;ldquo;We have been thrilled to improve Husqvarna processes in Beatrice,&amp;rdquo; Rucker said. &amp;ldquo;We believe we can achieve similar results at the cornerstone of their U.S. presence in Orangeburg.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Based in Raleigh, N.C., Rucker &amp;amp; Associates is a high-performance consultancy dedicated to helping companies discover dramatic new efficiencies using Lean Manufacturing and Six Sigma improvement methodologies. Rucker&amp;rsquo;s hands-on mentoring process with clients produces dramatic results &amp;ndash; training teams to accelerate change and implement continuous improvement. Every Rucker project features an unconditional guarantee.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	The Husqvarna Group is the world&amp;#39;s largest producer of outdoor power products including chainsaws, trimmers, lawn mowers and garden tractors. It is the European leader in consumer irrigation equipment under the Gardena brand. The Group is also one of the world leaders in cutting equipment and diamond tools for the construction and stone industries. Net sales in 2009 were SEK 34 billion and the average number of employees was 15,000 in 42 countries.&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/continuous_improvement/~4/QrJy12dDmkw" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2011-04-08T14:10:29-05:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/28422/Husqvarna%20Turning%20to%20Lean%20Manufacturing" />
        <feedburner:origLink>http://reliableplant.com/Read/28422/Husqvarna%20Turning%20to%20Lean%20Manufacturing</feedburner:origLink></item>
        <item>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:noria.com,2010-06-10:publishing:magazines:rp:6413fb70-fc79-4c5c-868a-9ebf00915523</guid>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/continuous_improvement/~3/_Iuv-h6LEDA/Worldwide%20Industrial%20adds%20grease%2c%20oil%20and%20lubricants%20to%20its%20marketplace</link>
            <a10:author>
                <a10:name>Noria Corporation</a10:name>
            </a10:author>
            <category>Industry News</category>
            <category>Articles</category>
            <title>Worldwide Industrial adds grease, oil and lubricants to its marketplace</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	Oxnard, California &amp;ndash; The American-Asia Import Export Industrial Trade Portal announced April 8 the addition of nearly 50 manufacturers and distributors of lube, oil and greases for its newly revised &lt;a href="http://www.worldwideindustrialmarketplace.com/directory/lubricants_petroleum.html"&gt;&lt;font color="#807d7a"&gt;Industrial Lubricants Suppliers&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Directory. The company, a division of Industrial Leaders said the vertical directory and guide includes a wide variety of oil lubricants, dielectric, lithium greases, synthetic &amp;amp; lubricating grease, white lithium, silicone, high temperature lube as well as other products to lubricate machinery, power transmission and motion control equipment in manufacturing facilities, power plants, construction sites, automotive and other applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Julio Perez, spokesman for Worldwide Industrial which founded the US-Asia Trade Portal nearly 10 years ago said company&amp;#39;s marketplace includes an &lt;a href="http://www.arrivenews.com/exhibitors/lubricants_petroleum.html"&gt;&lt;font color="#807d7a"&gt;Industrial Lubricants Guide&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with additional offerings from suppliers across the globe. According to Perez, the grease, oils and lube on the site is suitable for automotive engines, conveyors, power equipment, bearings, heavy machinery, motion control, automated factory machines &amp;amp; robots, hydraulic presses, forklifts, pneumatic systems, pumps, chains, fittings, gears &amp;amp; shafts, springs, diesel motors, machine tools, metalworking, electrical equipment, compressors, transformers and a broad range of other products and industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;ldquo;The standard and synthetic oils, greases and other lubricants offered by Worldwide Industrial is suitable for virtually all consumer, aerospace, vehicle, military, commercial and industrial markets designed, formulated and produced by domestic and international manufacturers,&amp;rdquo; said Perez.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;ldquo;Most recently Worldwide Industrial added several suppliers of a specialized low temperature and high temperature lubricant designed for the metalworking industry such as lubricating film on metal parts as used by machine shops, industrial engineers and others working with metals.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Perez said limited advertising space is currently available in the directory for qualified manufacturers and distributors of oils, greases and other lubricants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Worldwide Industrial is a US-Asia industrial import and export trade portal created to connect U.S. and Asian buyers and suppliers of industrial supplies, machine tools, equipment and materials for the manufacturing community. The site includes offerings primarily from companies in the United States, China and India at &lt;a href="http://www.worldwideindustrialmarketplace.com"&gt;http://www.worldwideindustrialmarketplace.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/continuous_improvement/~4/_Iuv-h6LEDA" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
